additional.message_subject: [PAID] Early Childhood Education Survey Follow-Up Interview
additional.message_body:
Hello,

Thank you for sharing your thoughts about early childhood education through our market research survey. We want to better understand the needs of families who utilize child care support and think you would be a great fit for a follow-up focus group discussion.

 

This discussion will be blinded among participants (i.e., you will not know who else is in the discussion nor will your identity be revealed). The focus group will consist of 8-10 individuals total and last 90 minutes.

The discussion in your area will be held virtually on Tuesday, March 26 from 7pm – 8:30pm CT.

 

 If you choose to participate and are selected, you will receive a [financial_data] Amazon gift card*. It’s our way of saying thank you for your feedback.

 

If you are interested in participating or have any questions/concerns, please email [email_address]

 

Thank you in advance for your consideration!

additional.message_body:
Hi Deletha,

 

Thank you for your interest in the focus group discussion. I wanted to confirm the below before we set you up for a discussion. Can you please confirm the following with a “yes” or “no”:

Do you currently have a child that is 5 or younger and still enrolled in a Pre-K program?
You indicated in the survey that you have a child that disenrolled from a [organization_name] brand ([organization_name], [organization_name], [organization_name], T[organization_name], [organization_name], and/or [organization_name]), did you disenroll this child because you moved OR because they aged into Kindergarten?

 

Thank you!
